   <p id="Par88" class="p">Substituting the abatement cost function and the abatement level derived from the equilibrium condition of Eq. 
    <xref rid="Equ41" ref-type="" class="xref">30</xref> in the resource constraint 
    <div id="IEq27" class="inline-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
     <alternatives class="alternatives" xmlns="">
      <tex-math id="M139" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {R}_i={P}_i{y}_i^c+{C}_i\left({A}_i\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M140" display="inline" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">R</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">=</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">P</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mi">y</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
        <span class="mi">c</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">C</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
       </div>
       <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
        <div class="msub">
         <span class="mi">A</span>
         <span class="mi">i</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span xlink:href="11027_2017_9758_Article_IEq27.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </div> gives an expression which can be numerically solved for the only unknown, consumption.
   </p>
   <p id="Par89" class="p">For the Nash outcome with a global permit market (denoted by superscript 
    <italic class="italic">NP</italic>), the permit price is not dependent on the permit allocation across countries, but only on the relative importance of climate quality versus income, for simplicity assumed to be uniform (so 
    <italic class="italic">α</italic>
    <sub xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
     <italic class="italic" xmlns="">i</italic>
    </sub> = 
    <italic class="italic">α</italic>), and the number of countries. Using Eq. 
    <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">8</xref>, it follows that
    <disp-formula id="Equ43" class="disp-formula">
     <label class="label">8</label>
     <alternatives class="alternatives">
      <tex-math id="M141" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {\sum}_{i=1}^n{P}_i\frac{u_A}{u_{y_i^c}}={nq}^{NP}\Rightarrow \alpha {Y}_w={nq}^{NP} $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M142" display="block" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mo">∑</span>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span width="0.12em" class="mspace"/>
         <span class="mi">i</span>
         <span class="mo">=</span>
         <span class="mn">1</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span width="0.12em" class="mspace"/>
         <span class="mi">n</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">P</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mfrac">
        <div class="msub">
         <span class="mi">u</span>
         <span class="mi">A</span>
        </div>
        <div class="msub">
         <span class="mi">u</span>
         <div class="msubsup">
          <span class="mi">y</span>
          <span class="mi">i</span>
          <span class="mi">c</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">=</span>
       <div class="msup">
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">nq</span>
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">⇒</span>
       <span class="mi">α</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">Y</span>
        <span class="mi">w</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">=</span>
       <div class="msup">
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">nq</span>
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <graphic xlink:href="11027_2017_9758_Article_Equ43.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </disp-formula>
   </p>
   <p id="Par90" class="p">Because of the permit market, marginal costs are uniform:
    <disp-formula id="Equ44" class="disp-formula">
     <label class="label">32</label>
     <alternatives class="alternatives">
      <tex-math id="M143" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {MC}_i^{NP}={q}^{NP}=-c\ln \left[1-\frac{A_i^{NP}}{E_i\left(1-{r}_i\right)}\right] $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M144" display="block" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">MC</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">=</span>
       <div class="msup">
        <span class="mi">q</span>
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">=</span>
       <span class="mo">−</span>
       <span class="mi">c</span>
       <span class="mo">ln</span>
       <div close="]" open="[" class="mfenced">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mn">1</span>
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <div class="mfrac">
          <div class="msubsup">
           <span class="mi">A</span>
           <span class="mi">i</span>
           <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mrow">
           <div class="msub">
            <span class="mi">E</span>
            <span class="mi">i</span>
           </div>
           <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
            <div class="mrow">
             <span class="mn">1</span>
             <span class="mo">−</span>
             <div class="msub">
              <span class="mi">r</span>
              <span class="mi">i</span>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <graphic xlink:href="11027_2017_9758_Article_Equ44.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </disp-formula>So for each country, the optimal abatement level
    <xref ref-type="fn" rid="Fn21" class="xref">21</xref> and abatement cost become
    <disp-formula id="Equ47" class="disp-formula">
     <label class="label">33</label>
     <alternatives class="alternatives">
      <tex-math id="M145" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {A}_i^{NP}={E}_i\left(1-{r}_i\right)\left(1-\exp \left(-{q}^{NP}/c\right)\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M146" display="block" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mi">A</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">=</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <span class="mi">E</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
       </div>
       <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mn">1</span>
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <div class="msub">
          <span class="mi">r</span>
          <span class="mi">i</span>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mn">1</span>
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span class="mo">exp</span>
         <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
          <div class="mrow">
           <span class="mo">−</span>
           <div class="msup">
            <span class="mi">q</span>
            <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
           </div>
           <span stretchy="true" class="mo">/</span>
           <span class="mi">c</span>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <graphic xlink:href="11027_2017_9758_Article_Equ47.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
     </alternatives>
    </disp-formula>
    <disp-formula id="Equ48" class="disp-formula">
     <label class="label">34</label>
     <alternatives class="alternatives">
      <tex-math id="M147" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ {C}_i^{NP}\left({A}_i^{NP}\right)=q\;\left({A}_i^{NP}-{E}_i\left(1-{r}_i\right)\right)+c\;{A}_i^{NP} $$\end{document}</tex-math>
      <div id="M148" display="block" class="math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
       <div class="msubsup">
        <span class="mi">C</span>
        <span class="mi">i</span>
        <span mathvariant="italic" class="mi">NP</span>
       </div>
       <div close=")" open="(" class="mfenced">
        <div class="msubsup">
         <span class="mi">A</span>
